title: Rob Wasserrman - [1994] Trios (FLAC)
description:
Rob Wasserman - Trios (FLAC)
Release Date: 1994


Review by Richard Meyer:
Bassist extraordinare picks up from the previous duets release with this set of trios. Most of these songs were written for this project, some even improvised on the spot as in the case of the Edie Brickell, Wasserman, Garcia cuts. Elvis Costello, along with Marc Ribot, are great. There are some bass instrumentals but the best is "Fantasy Is Reality" written by Sam Philips and Brian Wilson and sung by his daughter Carnie.

2. Put Your Big Toe In The Milk Of Human Kindness (Ft. Elvis Costello / Marc Ribot)
3. White-Wheeled Limousine (Ft. Bruce Hornsby / Branford Marsalis)
4. Country
5. Zillionaire (Ft. Edie Brickell / Jerry Garcia)
6. Dustin' Off The Bass (Ft. Willie Dixon / Al Duncan)
7. Easy Answers (Ft. Bob Weir / Neil Young)
8. Satisfaction (Bass Triolgy Part 2)
9. Home Is Where You Get Across (Ft. Les Claypool / Chris Whitley)
10. Spike's Bulls (Bass Triolgy Part 3)
11. Gypsy One (Ft. Matt Haimovitz / Joan Jeanrenaud)
12. Gypsy Two (Ft. Matt Haimovitz / Joan Jeanrenaud)
